# Page title of discover page
msgid "Welcome to the Mascot Kingdom!"
msgstr ""

msgid "Karts. Nitro. Action! SuperTuxKart is a 3D open-source arcade racer with a variety of characters, tracks, and modes to play. Our aim is to create a game that is more fun than realistic, and provide an enjoyable experience for all ages."
msgstr ""

msgid "In Story mode, you must face the evil Nolok, and defeat him in order to make the Mascot Kingdom safe once again! You can race by yourself against the computer, compete in several Grand Prix cups, or try to beat your fastest time in Time Trial mode. You can also race, battle or play soccer with up to eight friends on a single computer, play on a local network or play online with other players all over the world."
msgstr ""

msgid "Main Characters"
msgstr ""

msgid "Tux"
msgstr ""

msgid "The hero of SuperTuxKart. Tux is a brave penguin who must save his friend, Gnu, from the evil clutches of Nolok. Tux is the mascot of Linux."
msgstr ""

msgid "Gnu"
msgstr ""

msgid "Tux's wise mentor, Gnu rides a flying carpet and lives peacefully in a pagoda. When Nolok captures him, the entire kingdom will try to save him. Gnu is the mascot of the GNU Project."
msgstr ""

msgid "Nolok"
msgstr ""

msgid "The villain of SuperTuxKart, Nolok is always concocting some sort of malevolent plan inside his fiery lava castle."
msgstr ""

msgid "Additional Characters"
msgstr ""

msgid "Sara"
msgstr ""

msgid "Sara is a powerful magician, and the ruler of the Mascot Kingdom. She races using a specialised snowmobile. She is the mascot of the OpenGameArt website."
msgstr ""

msgid "Wilber"
msgstr ""

msgid "Wilber is the official cameraman who works for WTXB-TV to record kart races, which are very popular in the Mascot Kingdom. He is the mascot of GIMP."
msgstr ""

msgid "Puffy"
msgstr ""

msgid "Puffy races mainly to earn enough money to accomplish his dream: to buy a submarine. He is the mascot of the OpenBSD project."
msgstr ""

msgid "Pidgin"
msgstr ""

msgid "Pidgin's ability to fly makes him perfect to deliver the results of the Grand Prix around the Mascot Kingdom. He is the mascot of Pidgin."
msgstr ""

msgid "Godette"
msgstr ""

msgid "Godette is the mascot of Godot and truly a tech girl. She is never seen without her friend, GDBot, a robot she built and programmed herself. They even race together in a unique tandem kart."
msgstr ""

msgid "Amanda"
msgstr ""

msgid "Amanda was rescued by monks when they found her in a basket as a cub. She now teaches the ancient art of racing in a monastery. She is the mascot of Window Maker."
msgstr ""

msgid "Emule"
msgstr ""

msgid "Emule's superior knowledge of mechanical engineering allowed him to build his own kart with a turbocharged engine. He is the mascot of eMule."
msgstr ""

msgid "Suzanne"
msgstr ""

msgid "Racing has been Suzanne's dream since childhood. She began her racing career in the prestigious Kart Academy of Val Verde. She is the mascot of Blender."
msgstr ""

msgid "Gavroche"
msgstr ""

msgid "Gavroche is a goblin that owns the Ravenbridge mansion. Sometimes he makes scary noises, tricking people into thinking the house is haunted. He is the mascot of MediaGoblin."
msgstr ""

msgid "Hexley"
msgstr ""

msgid "Hexley's ancestors started kart racing many years ago, and generation after generation, they became very good at it. He is the mascot of Darwin."
msgstr ""

msgid "Xue"
msgstr ""

msgid "Xue likes to stand out from the crowd, and her unusual kart reflects this. She races a special hovercraft, which is small enough to be driven by a mouse. She is the mascot of XFCE."
msgstr ""

msgid "Konqi"
msgstr ""

msgid "While Konqi's ancient ancestors were dangerous and feared, dragons today are harmless... mostly. He is the mascot of the KDE project."
msgstr ""

msgid "Adiumy"
msgstr ""

msgid "Adiumy started kart racing when he realized his legs are too short to be a soccer star. Although the other mascots sometimes make fun of his waddling gait, he is highly respected as one of the most talented racing drivers in the kingdom. Adiumy is the mascot of Adium."
msgstr ""

msgid "Kiki"
msgstr ""

msgid "A Krita user first drew Kiki for a training manual, but as soon as the manual was printed, Kiki decided to jump off the pages and race around the world on her pen-powered aeroplane. Kiki is the mascot of the Krita digital painting program."
msgstr ""

msgid "Pepper"
msgstr ""

msgid "Pepper is a little witch who loves playing with her cat Carrot. Her enthusiasm for racing ignited when her friend Kiki helped her to tune her broom with a nitro injection system and custom exhaust tips. Pepper is the main character of the Pepper & Carrot project."
msgstr ""

msgid "...And many more!"
msgstr ""

msgid "You can create your own characters, tracks, and arenas and share them with the SuperTuxKart community! You can do this by going to [online.supertuxkart.net](https://online.supertuxkart.net)."
msgstr ""

msgid "If you are interested you can take a look at the [community](Community) page."
msgstr ""

# Section title in the Donate page
msgid "Donating to SuperTuxKart"
msgstr ""

# Donate page - avoid double-quotes to not break the layout!
msgid "If you enjoyed SuperTuxKart and would like to help the project, or just to say thank you, you may donate to help us! SuperTuxKart now uses itch.io to receive donations. Click on the 'Download Now' button and you will be able to select your donation amount."
msgstr ""

# Donate page
msgid "Donations help us improve the game, as they may be used for purchasing hardware, file hosting and distribution services, servers to host websites, paying artists to produce improved artwork, and more. You can learn more about our policy [here](Donation_Policy)."
msgstr ""

# Donate page
msgid "Do not hesitate to contact us if you have any questions or problems!"
msgstr ""

# Section title in the Donate page
msgid "Gift Package"
msgstr ""

# Donate page
msgid "Alongside SuperTuxKart 1.5, a donation package including two tracks developed for SuperTuxKart Evolution - Drainage Dash and Freytra Peaks - is available for donations of 5$ or more."
msgstr ""

# Donate page - avoid double-quotes to not break the layout!
msgid "To install the package, first retrieve the '1.5 Gift Package' on itch.io, unzip the file, and follow the instructions in the included README. The procedure follows the [manual addons installation](Installing_Add-Ons) procedure."
msgstr ""

# Donate page
msgid "Unfortunately as of now, we are not able to offer an in-game installation procedure or a simple installation procedure for Android users. We are aware of this limitation, but we didn't want to delay 1.5's release to all users to solve it."
msgstr ""

# Section title in the Donate page
msgid "Other donation methods"
msgstr ""

# Donate page
msgid "Several community members have requested other methods to help fund SuperTuxKart."
msgstr ""

# Donate page
msgid "We are looking into ways to make recurrent donations possible."
msgstr ""

# Donate page
msgid "As a response to the request for more anonymous methods, we have established a way to donate using cryptocurrencies. Simply follow the instruction below. Everything is handled on supertuxkart.net! At the end of the process, you will also be able to retrieve the gift package."
msgstr ""

# Donate page
msgid "Please note that the minimum donation with this method is higher to avoid overhead from tiny transactions."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "This page documents SuperTuxKart's policy regarding donations and what we do with money received. These policies might change at any time depending on the requirements and the priorities of the project."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "However, you may rest assured that the team will not spend money on inconsequential things. All spending decisions are fully discussed among the members of the team ahead of time in order to avoid disagreements."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy - section title
msgid "Compensating developers and artists"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "A common characteristic of libre and open-source projects that compete successfuly with proprietary alternatives - such as Blender, OBS, Krita, and Lichess - is the use of donations to make development sustainable."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "SuperTuxKart has achieved much through the passion of volunteers. However, to realize its full potential and offer the community the new content and features it desires, it needs to be more than a hobby."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "Some of our developers and artists are willing to dedicate significantly more time to the game, but have to balance this desire with the risk of burnout and the need of a livelihood. Financial support allows to reconcile those concerns. It could also allow the project to hire external specialists for highly specialized tasks."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "Donations therefore mean faster and more sustainable development. For context, modern commercial racing games usually employ dozens of artists and developers. The SuperTuxKart project aims to do more with less, but your donations are the key for an open-source game that competes with them."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "All decisions regarding compensation are decided on a case-by-case basis and discussed within the team to reach a consensus. Compensation depends on the project's funds, the scope of the work, and the contributor's long-term commitment to the project."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "Of course, SuperTuxKart continues to warmly welcome anyone willing to volunteer through art, code, etc. Tomorrow's core contributors will grow from today's volunteers."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy - section title
msgid "Online infrastructure"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "Donations are used to cover the costs inherent to SuperTuxKart's online infrastructure."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "This includes domain name fees, and server hosting costs for:"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "The main website - crucial for the game's promotion and distribution"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "The addons website - responsible for addons distribution, online accounts, and online multiplayer"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "The official forum - a place to exchange with other players and ask questions"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "Official game servers - ranked races"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "Likewise, donations may be used to cover fees required for the distribution of SuperTuxKart on some platforms, such as Android and iOS."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy - section title
msgid "Hardware and software"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "The project may acquire specific hardware if it serves the game's development, such as:"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "Better computer components (CPU, GPU, monitor...) to improve the workflow of a developer or an artist"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "Hardware with which we want to improve SuperTuxKart's compatibility"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "Etc."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "The project may also pay licenses for professional software for which no suitable free alternative exists, particularly for assets creation."
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy - section title
msgid "Marketing and promotion"
msgstr ""

# Donation Policy page
msgid "Donations may also be used to cover costs (travel, etc.) related to representing SuperTuxKart in events such as gaming conventions and open source conferences."
msgstr ""

